<HEADLINE>
FT  20 APR 93 / Construction output to fall further
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CONSTRUCTION output will fall further this year than had been expected, an
industry forecasting body said yesterday, Andrew Taylor writes.
The National Council of Building Material Producers said it expected output
to fall by 2.5 per cent this year. It had been forecasting a 1.5 per cent
decline.
The group blamed the outlook on a worse-than-expected decline in commercial
property building and the government's delay in giving approval for the
Pounds 1.7bn Jubilee Underground line extension in London.
