<HEADLINE>
FT  20 APR 93 / Swiss outlook
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Switzerland's decision not to join the European Economic Area will probably
be less damaging to its economy than originally feared, the Basle Business
Cycle Research Group said yesterday, Reuter reports.
It reported that the economy was likely to contract by around 0.4 per cent
this year, before recovering in 1994 with 1 per cent growth. But it thought
the growth gap with the rest of western Europe would be only 0.6 percentage
point, compared with the 1 per centage point it estimated last October.
