   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Boris Yeltsin, campaigning for popular support in a referendum
next weekend, won the backing of some of Russia's most powerful trade unions
yesterday, Reuter reports from Moscow.
'The free trade unions call on all their members and other Russian citizens.
. . to confirm their political trust in the president and to vote for early
