Next Sunday's referendum will ask the people if they support Mr Yeltsin and
his reform policies and whether they favour early presidential and
parliamentary elections.
Mr Yeltsin yesterday met representatives of about 30 unions in the Kremlin.
They included miners from western Siberia's Kuzbass field, traditional
supporters of the president, as well as dockers and civil aviation workers.
