<TEXT>
FIRST BOSTON and Merrill Lynch, the US investment banks, have won the
mandate to act as global co-ordinators in the privatisation of YPF,
Argentina's national oil company. The sell-off will be Argentina's largest
privatisation.
Mr Daniel Marx, Argentina's top financial negotiator, said no decision had
