FT  19 APR 93 / Observer: Dream time
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Things must be looking up at Saatchi &amp; Saatchi, the worldwide advertising
giant. The Saatchi Brothers are starting to generate Big Ideas again.
Maurice Saatchi, who once toyed with the idea of buying Midland Bank for
Pounds 3bn, appears to be getting itchy fingers once more.
Ivan Fallon, the Saatchis'J well-connected biographer, reported in
yesterday's Sunday Times that Maurice wants to buy Express Newspapers, the
two national flagships in Lord Stevens' United Newspapers empire. A price of
around Pounds 200m has been mooted but this is a fraction of what they are
worth and there is no sign of any backers.
It sounds like this might have been one of those rather long cocktail
conversations that got out of hand. Lord Stevens has chatted with Maurice
but is still not sure whether he was joking or not.
Could this be a smokescreen while Sir Nicholas and Lady Lloyd, the husband
and wife team editing the Daily and Sunday Express, dream up their rumoured
management buy-out?
